data.description: Located in Cimarron at the back of a cul-de-sac is this grand 2858 sqft home featuring 4 bedrooms, 3.5 bathrooms and 3 car garage. The .25 acre lot backs up to the greenbelt and is walking distance to Del Cobre Park. While much of the home is original, the high tray ceilings, subtle arches, double sided fireplace, split staircase, abundance of windows supplying natural light and plenty of storage are just a few of the features which gives this property the potential to make it your forever home! Walking up to the front of the house you feel invited to "sit down and stay awhile" and enjoy the views from the front porch. The minute you enter through the front door your eyes are drawn upwards to the large windows and high tray ceiling. The abundance of natural light, tray ceilings and subtle arches throughout the lower level and upstairs in the primary suite gives a grand feel to this home. The kitchen features a large pantry, double ovens and two islands, one for cooking and the other with seating perfect for hosting your next get-together. There is a dual sided gas log fireplace which splits the formal living and family rooms. There is a split staircase which allows access to either to family room/kitchen or to the entry/living room. Whichever part of the house you are in there is convenient way to access upstairs. Right off the entry is a large room that could be used as a formal dining room or library/den. Upstairs you will find both a primary and junior suite each with its own bathroom and walk-in-closet. The other two bedrooms are Jack and Jill style, separated by a full bathroom. All bedrooms are upstairs allowing the separation between living and sleeping space. The front yard has low maintenance artificial turf for some year round greenery.  With some imagination, the backyard has the potential to become your  oasis. While most of the home is original, the layout and potential of this property make it a must see!
